<section>
  <h2>TMD monolayers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Direct band gap semiconductors</li>
    <li><strong>Break inversion symmetry</strong> ⇒ gapped out spectrum</li>
    <li><strong>Two inequivalent valleys </strong> ⇒ new degree of freedom</li>
    <li><strong>Strong spin-orbit coupling</strong> ⇒
        large valance band spin-splitting</li>
    <li>Opposite valley Berry curvature</li>
    <li>Optical valley probe and valley Hall effect</li>
    <li>Two state tight binding model:
        \( d_{z^2} \), and \( d_{xy} \pm i d_{x^2 - y^2} \)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    $$
    H_0^{\tau s} \left( \mathbf{k} \right) =
    a t \left(\tau k_x s_x + k_y s_y \right) \otimes I_2
    $$$$
    + \frac{\Delta}{2} s_z \otimes I_2
    - \lambda \tau \left(\sigma_z - 1 \right) \otimes S_z
    $$
  </p>
  {{cite references id="PhysRevLett.108.196802"}}
</section>

